Americans spent Sunday on lockdown as the U.S. toll from the novel coronavirus pandemic surpassed 21,300 deaths and more than half a million confirmed cases over the Easter weekend.
(Graphic: https://tmsnrt.rs/2w7hX9T)As the death toll has mounted, President Donald Trump mulled over when the country might begin to see a return to normality.
In some states, that has sparked legal battles over whether there should be exceptions to attend Easter services in person.
Southern Europe and the United States, whose death toll of over 20,600 is now the world's highest, have been the recent focal points of the pandemic.
While some nations think about a pandemic exit strategy, others are dealing with alarming rises in infections or deaths.